it.polimi.deib.se2019.sanp4.adrenaline.controller.requests

Class CompletableChoice<T extends Serializable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.deib.se2019.sanp4.adrenaline.controller.requests.CompletableChoice<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the choice

    public class CompletableChoice<T extends Serializable>
extends Object
    Represents the "promise" of a value in response to a ChoiceRequest highly inspired by CompletableFuture. A CompletableChoice can be returned when asking for a choice that has to be performed asynchronously (e.g. by the user).

    The method that received the CompletableChoice can then call get(), which will wait for the choice to be completed (it is a blocking method) and then return it.

    On the other hand the choice can be completed by calling complete(Object), which will complete the choice with the given object (if it is a valid choice) and return in via get().

    The CompletableChoice can also be cancelled, in which case the ones waiting on get() will receive an exception.

    Author:
    Alessandro Fulgini

        Parameters:

      • cancel

        public CompletableChoice<T> cancel()
        Attempts to cancel the choice. This attempt will fail if the choice has already been completed or cancelled.

        After this method returns, subsequent calls to isCompleted() will always return true. Subsequent calls to isCancelled() will always return true if this method returned true.

        Returns:
        this completable choice
